I was waiting for her at the corner of 1st Ave S and 1st Street S, and as she approached the corner she tripped over an elevated sidewalk slab and fell to the ground hitting her forehead and nose very hard. She was in severe pain and bleeding from her forehead and nose, so I called 911. I looked at the sidewalk where she had tripped and noticed that the sidewalk was not flat, unfortunately a sidewalk slab had become elevated due to a bulging tree root, and was now a trip hazard. The  911 medics responded quickly and were professional and supportive. They recommended that we go to the ER ASAP.  Luckily, the ER doctors found that her bones were not broken, and her bleeding wounds were not critical, and she was neurologically intact. So we were allowed to take her home, thankfully. description:
Hello,

The traffic light at Tampa road and US Highway 19 works. 

It works so well that you're enjoying the functionality for 45 minutes at a red light in the left turn lane to turn onto Lake St George. 

Every return trip from walmart, 45 minute wait.

Every return trip from Publix, 45 minute wait. 

Every return trip from target, 45 minute wait. 

Obviously not actually 45 minutes, but it sure seems like it. It's converted to dog minutes for dramatic effect. 

Now, I get it. Grass is greener on the other side... I would just prefer to not watch it grow from an inch to an inch and 1/2 in the time I'm at the light. 

I've seen turtles cross 6 lanes of busy road faster than it takes for me to get through this light turning left onto lake St George. 

In the time it took at this light the USA deficit was fixed and there was world peace. 

Not to brag and flex my non existent power and figurative title... but I'm also the HOA president for Lake St George. 

Can I extend some figurative non existent Executive power and please convert this light to a blinking yellow turn after 6pm or 7pm?

Blinking yellow from 11am to 3pm? and also from 7pm to 6am? 

I know this request is drawn out and a full blown descriptive story... Im writing it while waiting to turn left onto Lake St George. 

Please save our sanity and add this to be a fabulous blinking yellow. 

I can't keep the pressure of thinking, If I go... will anyone know? But then don't because I know PCSO are like ninjas hiding behind every bush and palm tree. 

It just turned green. 

Warmest, 
Impatient in Palm Harbor

Window openings on east side of house at 10410 115th Ave., Largo, FL 33773 are permanently secured in violation of the Pinellas County housing code.
Sec. 22-299 (7) states: No window, exterior door or casement that is secured by plywood, boards, or other protective covering, whether of a permanent or temporary nature, may remain so secured for longer than a period of 90 days, unless such protective covering is a professionally manufactured product made solely for purposes of storm protection.
Also, Sec. 22-297 states that while year-round, mechanically ventilating conditioned air systems may be substituted for windows in rooms other than rooms used for sleeping purposes, window type air-conditioning units are not included in this exception.

INADEQUATE WARNING OF BIKERS CROSSING TRINITY BOULEVARD I am submitting this on Pinellas Click Fix because Pasco Click Fix does not acknowledge that this is an area with services.  If you are not the appropriate agency, please forward to who is.

We pushed the signal which starts the yellow flashing lights at the crossing.  We checked the status of the traffic to ensure that the drivers in both directions were stopping before proceeding.
